related.description: Penn rules the day at the tripleheader in the Palstra, and things are definitely looking up for the Quakers.
related.title: Penn finds motivation, and a bright future
related.headline: Penn finds motivation, and a bright future

article.headline: Penn cruises past Temple
article.linkText: Penn routs Temple as winless Owls reach new low
article.story:
PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Guard David Klatsky came off the bench to
score a career-high 18 points, and Andrew Toole had 14 as Penn
crushed crosstown rival Temple 71-46 on Saturday night.

Klatsky was 4-for-5 from beyond the 3-point arc and Penn (2-2),
which was 20-of-65 from 3-point range coming into the game, made
15-of-27 in the win.

Jeff Schiffner had 12 points, Ugonna Onyekwe scored 10 and Tim
Begley added nine assists for Penn, which has now beaten Temple
three of the last five times after losing 17 straight from
1982-1998.

Temple (0-5) is off to its worst start in the 107-year history
of the program.

Alex Wesby had a career-high 27 points for the Owls.

The game was the third in a tripleheader, the Big Five Classic,
held at the Palestra. All three Division I schools in the
Philadelphia area played, with Saint Joseph's defeating Drexel
50-37 and Villanova beating La Salle 74-71.

The Quakers scored the first 13 points of the game and led by 25
at halftime. Klatsky, who scored the final five points of the half
to cap a 9-0 run, had 13 before the break. Penn was 16-of-25 (64
percent) from the field in the first half.

Temple made 5-of-17 (30 percent) from the field in the first
half, with Wesby scoring 9 on 4-of-6 shooting.

Penn's lead reached 30 in the second half when a 3-pointer by
Toole made it 53-23 with 15:18 left in the game. A 3-pointer by
Schiffner made it 59-26 later in the half.
